content:
Use the CRM Analytics connectors to connect data inside and outside of Salesforce. You can access data in your local org and external Salesforce orgs, apps, data warehouses, and database services.

After you connect to a data source, configure data sync to extract the needed source data into connected objects. You can then prepare the data in these connected objects using a recipe to create your final dataset.

Connect to Local Salesforce Data
Use the Salesforce Connector to manage the data synced between your local Salesforce org and CRM Analytics.

Connect to Data Outside of Salesforce
Create a remote connection to sync external data with CRM Analytics.

Pre-Pull Data for Recipes with Data Sync
Use data sync to pull data to CRM Analytics on a regular schedule. By scheduling sync from Salesforce and remote systems ahead of time, your recipes have less to do and run faster.
title: Connect and Sync Data to CRM Analytics
